01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>8:16:19 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valasclose2.jpg width=150 hieght=150></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Balance</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ice spear has a long recast delay.  If you were to just cast Ice spear, it would take forever to kill anything. There is no valid reason Ice spear needs such a long delay.<br>
<br>
Sunstrike on the other hand pops back instanly after fireing so you can cast one right after the other.  Draughts have a short recast delay but there is still a recast delay.<br>
<br>
The reason I say to finish off mobs with Ice spear is because its 1200 dam in 4 seconds vs suntrike 1615 dam in 7 seconds.  Ice spear is much faster, but since it has a long recast, its best used as the killing shot so you don't have to worry about the after-delay.   I hope that made sense.<br>
<br>
</font><P>Valas Defai<BR>
